key.name: org.pentaho.reporting.engine.classic.extensions.datasources.mondrian.MembersOnAxisSorted
key.description:
Defines whether members on an axis are sorted by dimension and hierarchy level. If set to 'false' members are sorted by access-order, which is determined by walking through the result set and recording the appearance of members on the axis. Access-order can return changing column orders depending on how the MDX query is structured.
This defaults to 'true' to give reports a well-defined column order that matches the results seen by other OLAP tools. Set this setting to 'false' to restore access-order, which was the default in older releases.
